gclone - Git Clone
USAGE:
    gclone <project-url>
DESCRIPTION:
    Clone a project in a standard location.
    Without a console context (ticket id), clones to ~/projects/<host>/<repo>.
    With a console context set (_CONSOLE_CONTEXT_ID), clones to
    ~/workspace/<ticket-id>/repos/<host>/<repo> and creates a branch named
    after the ticket id from conf_git_workspace_base_branch (default: dev).
ARGUMENTS:
    project-url
        URL of the git repository to clone
CONFIGURATION:
    conf_git_workspace_base_path
        Root directory for ticket workspaces (default: ~/workspace)
    conf_git_workspace_base_branch
        Branch to create the ticket branch from (default: dev)
EXAMPLES:
    gclone https://github.com/user/repo.git
    gclone git@github.com:user/repo.git
